





	

	


	


In summary, there are three categorical covariates which are specified next.Lineage: a two-level factor that classifies animals as reactive (R+) or not reactive(R-) to temporary social isolation;Session: a three-level factor that defines theexperimental session (session 1, session 2 or session 3);Moment: a three-level factorthat defines whether or not the animal was under human intervention (pre, duringor post brushing). The number of ear posture changes and the time performing thehorizontal ear posture were registered in each moment and in eachsession. By thisway, each animal contributed for the final data set with nine records, such that wehave repeated measures from the same sheep.





